well, the initial velocity is 20m/s and final is 25m/s so the change in velocity is 5m/s. That means that every second the velocity is changing 5m/s. And the change in velocity per second is called acceleration which in this case is 5m/s/s which is equal to 5m/s2. So the ball in case 2 is accelerating by 5m/s2 and the change in velocity per second is 5m/s.
It's 5m/s2 because that's the unit of acceleration . You know it changed from 20- 25 and it increased. So any increase is acceleration so the unit of acceleration is m/s2
